s\n+\n+Accepted\n+\n+## Context\n+\n+Project Manager must support durable project state and cross-project queries by name, type, mode, lifecycle, phase, activity, health, delivery, attention, owner, domain, and tags.\n+\n+The workspace contains heterogeneous projects and capability packages, so a single repository-level build or project model is not sufficient.\n+\n+## Decision\n+\n+Each managed project owns `.agent-project/project.json` as its source of truth.\n+\n+Project Manager maintains a generated global `registry.json` for fast query and dashboard-style listing.\n+\n+## Consequences\n+\n+- Project state stays near the project.\n+- The registry can be rebuilt from project files.\n+- Queries can be fast without scanning the workspace every time.\n+- The model can support both finite and ongoing projects.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\project-manager\\.agent-project\\tasks\\task-0001.json","relativePath":"agent_workspace/capability-library/agent-system-rules/project-manager/.agent-project/tasks/task-0001.json","type":"add","patch":"Index: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\project-manager\\.agent-project\\tasks\\task-0001.json\n===================================================================\n--- D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\project-manager\\.agent-project\\tasks\\task-0001.json\n+++ D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\project-manager\\.agent-project\\tasks\\task-0001.json\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+{\n+  \"id\": \"task-0001\",\n+  \"title\": \"Build project-manager v0.1\",\n+  \"type\": \"implement\",\n+  \"status\": \"review\",\n+  \"priority\": \"high\",\n+  \"phase\": \"validation\",\n+  \"owner\": \"assistant\",\n+  \"depends_on\": [],\n+  \"blocks\": [],\n+  \"tags\": [\"schema\", \"registry\", \"query\", \"mycli\"],\n+  \"acceptance_criteria\": [\n+    \"Project-manager package exists under agent-system-rules\",\n+    \"